And the JS like this (not sure exactly where I got this, so I can't credit the original author here).

```
// accordion
$('.accordion> h4').click(function() {
    // remove the active class from all buttons
    $('.accordion> h4').removeClass('active');
    // we close all open divs
    $('.accordion> div').slideUp('normal');
    // we open the next div
    if($(this).next().is(':hidden') == true) {
        // add the active class to the button
        $(this).addClass('active');
        // open the div
        $(this).next().slideDown('normal');
    }
});
// close all divs on open
$('.accordion> div').hide();
```

A bit of CSS and it looks more or less the same as Bootstrap. I think it's simple and requires much less markup. Do you think the default accordion could be simplified further in a future release? Consider this a feature request :)

