I implemented the Bootstrap popover on a site I'm building, using the toggle method.

http://andy.goba.mobi/

It contains a form encouraging users to input their phone number to receive a download link for our mobile app. In Chrome 17.0.963.38 beta, mobile safari (iOS), and Safari 5.1.2 it behaves as expected. I click the trigger link, and the modal opens. Clicking anywhere on the page does nothing until I click the trigger again to close the window.

In Firefox the modal behaves erratically. On initial load a single click opens, then closes the modal. A subsequent click opens the modal, but clicking into it (or anywhere else on the page) causes it to close. It then repeats that pattern.

1st click - opens a closes the modal
2nd click - closes the modal
lather rinse repeat.

This is the code I'm using to implement the popover:

```
        $('.module h2 a').popover({
            trigger:'toggle',
            html: true,
            offset: 28,
            placement: 'above',
            content: function(what){
                return $('#fSubmitForm').html();
            }
        })
        .click(function(e){
            e.preventDefault();
            // open the popover
            $(this).popover('toggle');
        });
```

